
==French==
===Etymology===
literaly "soft-cutting"
===Noun===
#[[line-engraving]], [[copper-plate engraving]]
#a type of [[engraving]] on [[copper]] [[plate]]s where the design is made up of a series of lines; its use was formerly common for postage stamps and paper currency.

===Usage notes===
*The French term is often used directly in English, where it should be italicized.

